It is said that Shirebrook has been on the map since the stone-age but its present prosperity is due to the coal industry. The pit was sunk at the end of the last century, and , because it seemed to be in the middle of nowhere, a complete mining village had to be built. Rows of terraced back-to-back houses were erected. A major redevelopment over the past few years has seen the disappearance of many of these houses with pleasant, open estates replacing them. The people of Shirebrook belong to a very warm-hearted, close-knit community. Most locals are born, brought up and will die within the boundaries of Shirebrook.
